net.sf.jlinkgrammar
Class ParseSet

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.jlinkgrammar.ParseSet

public class ParseSet
extends java.lang.Object

The first thing we do is we build a data structure to represent the result of the entire parse search. There will be a set of nodes built for each call to the count() function that returned a non-zero value, AND which is part of a valid linkage. Each of these nodes represents a valid continuation, and contains pointers to two other sets (one for the left continuation and one for the righ continuation).
